ce:section.ce:para:
The stability of the proposed aptasensor was also evaluated. The fabricated aptasensor response was 87% of its initial activity after it had been stored in refrigerator at 4 °C for 14 days. Furthermore, the reproducibility of the proposed aptasensor was tested also with 5 electrodes which produced under the same conditions. The RSD was calculated to be 3.18%, confirming that the results are reproducible (Fig. 6
                        ). To estimate the high selectivity of the method, different interferences such as amoxicillin, ciprofloxacin and gentamicin are challenged. As depicted in Fig. 7
                        , all the interferences create much lower signal compared with that of STR, demonstrating the excellent selectivity.
